`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
When decomposing large UI components into subpackages, the key is finding natural "seams" — self-contained sections that can become standalone components with explicit props. For PauseMenu, the three tabs (Stats, Progress, Settings) are ideal seams. For AchievementPopup, the store logic vs render logic split is the seam. For GameUI, all `useMemo` computed values form a natural data hook.
